<HEADLINE>
<P>
MABEL EBY; OVERSAW SEATING AT ACADEMY AWARDS CEREMONIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mabel Eby, 78, who oversaw the always sensitive ticket distributions and 
seating arrangements for 44 annual Academy Award presentations and the 
longest-serving employee at the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences.She 
came to the academy in 1945, when it was at Hollywood and Vine before moving to 
Beverly Hills. She retired in 1988 and was credited with knowing more film 
stars and executives than most of the industry members she served. In Beverly 
Hills on Thursday after a long illness. 
</P>
