<HEADLINE>
<P>
YOUTH SLAIN IN VENICE GANG SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 18-year-old man was fatally shot early Sunday outside a party at a Venice 
housing project, in what Los Angeles police are calling a gang-related 
shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said a gunman drove past the Marionwood public housing complex about 3 
a.m. and fired several shots at Manuel Hernandez as the teen-ager tried to run 
for cover. 
</P>
<P>
 Hernandez, who lived in the housing project and had been attending the party, 
was hit in the upper and lower body. He was pronounced dead at Harbor-UCLA 
Medical Center, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Sunday that they had no information about the shooting from 
witnesses. "Everyone knows (Hernandez), but no one is talking," Detective 
Cedric Wilder said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the shooting was gang-related but do not know what gang Hernandez 
belonged too. 
</P>
</TEXT>
