<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; HUMMINGBIRDS PROGRAM PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 People who want to learn more about hummingbirds are invited to a special 
program April 21 at the Fountain Valley branch library. 
</P>
<P>
 Authors Robert and Esther Tyrrell will present the 7 p.m. program and share 
information about nature's small, colorful birds. The couple have devoted more 
than 17 years to the study of hummingbirds. 
</P>
<P>
 The free program, "Hummingbirds: Jewels in the Sky," will feature a slide 
presentation followed by a question-and-answer session. 
</P>
<P>
 The authors will share stories of their travels to jungles and crocodile 
swamps in search of these birds. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is sponsored by the Friends of Fountain Valley Branch Library. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 962-1324. 
</P>
<P>
 The library is at 17635 Los Alamos St., behind City Hall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
