<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; CLUB TO HONOR TOP OFFICER, FIREFIGHTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The public is invited to attend an awards ceremony April 20 to honor the 
city's top police officer and firefighter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Exchange Club of Fountain Valley is hosting the annual event, which begins 
at 11:30 a.m. in the grand ballroom at Los Caballeros Racquet & Sports Club, 
17272 Newhope St. 
</P>
<P>
 This year's honorees are senior police officer James Perry and 
firefighter-engineer Ron Chamberlain. 
</P>
<P>
 The cost of the luncheon is $15 per person. 
</P>
<P>
 For reservations, call Police Capt. Bill DeNisi, Exchange Club president, at 
(714) 965-4452 or the Fire Department at (714) 965-4436. 
</P>
</TEXT>
