<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; YOUTH CLUB TO HOLD ANNUAL FUND-RAISER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Boys & Girls Club, which provides education and sports programs to more 
than 2,000 youngsters each year, is holding its annual fund-raiser April 23 and 
hopes to raise more than $70,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will include a silent auction, a dinner, a live auction and dancing, 
said Jerry Younker, one of the fund-raiser's planners.Among the auction items 
are a new Thunderbird, artwork and trips to the Bahamas, Nashville and New 
Orleans. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is $75 per person for the fund-raiser, which will be at the 
Doubletree Hotel, 100 S. The City Drive, Orange. For tickets, call the Boys & 
Girls Club at (714) 525-8241. 
</P>
<P>
 The nonprofit youth club raised about $50,000 last year and hopes to have 300 
people attend this event, Younker said. About half the tickets have already 
been sold. 
</P>
<P>
 The club, at 348 W. Commonwealth Ave., offers programs for youths ages 6 to 
18, mostly during after-school hours. It is also busy weekends and in the 
summer. 
</P>
<P>
 Besides sports programs, the club also offers tutoring, anti-gang and 
anti-drug programs, arts and crafts and a computer center. Programs for 
preschool children are offered at a branch of the club at 410 S. Richman Ave. 
WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
