<HEADLINE>
<P>
JONES POWERS NORTHRIDGE TO SWEEP OF ARIZONA STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Third baseman Shannon Jones tied two Cal State Northridge softball records 
Sunday by hitting two home runs and driving in six runs in the second game of 
the Matadors' doubleheader sweep of Arizona State. 
</P>
<P>
 CSUN won the first game, 2-1 in eight innings, and the second, 10-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones, who also homered in the first game and has eight for the season, hit 
the fourth grand slam in Matador history in the sixth inning of the second 
game. It was the sixth two-homer game by a Matador player. Her six runs batted 
in tied the mark set by Leslie Barrett in March 1982 and tied 10 years later by 
current Matador outfielder Beth Calcante. 
</P>
<P>
 Calcante won the first game by hitting her fifth homer of the season to lead 
off eighth inning. 
</P>
<P>
 The sixth-ranked Matadors (33-6) led, 1-0, in the first game on the strength 
of Jones' homer before Arizona State (16-29) scored an unearned run in the 
seventh. 
</P>
<P>
 Amy Windmiller (18-1) allowed seven hits and struck out seven to earn the 
victory in the first game. Kathy Blake (10-5) was the winner in the second 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones and Calcante finished the day with five hits apiece. Catcher Scia 
Maumausolo had three hits in the second game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
