<P>
NEWSWIRE: PAEZ FIGHTS AT FORUM WITH EYE TO DE LA HOYA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS BAKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jorge Paez of Mexicali, Mexico, a former International Boxing Federation 
featherweight champion, takes on Mauricio Aceves of Mexico City in a 10-round 
lightweight fight tonight at the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
 If Paez, 49-6-4 with 34 knockouts, wins his next two fights, he probably will 
box Oscar De La Hoya this summer.Aceves, a former WBO lightweight champion, is 
26-12-1 with 20 knockouts. 
</P>
<P>
 There are two other fights on tonight's card, which begins at 7:30. David 
Dixon of Los Angeles meets Mike Faulkner of Memphis in a heavyweight bout and 
unbeaten Jorge Monzon of Mexico City meets Roberto Chala of Colombia in a 
featherweight fight. 
</P>
<P>
 Dixon, who has won his last six fights, five by knockout, is 17-2 with 15 
knockouts. Faulkner is 11-8 with eight knockouts. Monzon is 12-0 with eight 
knockouts, and Chala is 7-5 with five knockouts. CHRIS BAKER 
