<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; TITAN GYMNASTS TO MISS NATIONALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cal State Fullerton women's gymnastics team narrowly missed advancing to 
the national finals Sunday in the West regional competition at Boise, Ida. 
</P>
<P>
 The top three teams advance, but the Titans finished fourth with 191.275 
points.Washington was third with 191.550 points. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA won with 194.300 points and Oregon State (193.550) was second. The top 
three teams advance to the NCAA championships, April 21-23 at Utah. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton's Celeste Delia was fourth overall with 38.950 points. Delia, who 
won the Big West all-around title earlier this season, was sixth in the floor 
exercise, seventh in the uneven bars, ninth in the balance beam, and 14th in 
the vault. 
</P>
<P>
 Cristi Clifford (38.450), also of Fullerton, was seventh. Both are expected to 
qualify for the national meet when the official field is announced today. 
</P>
<P>
 Chari Knight of Oregon State won the overall title with 39.400 points. She won 
the balance beam and the floor exercise. 
</P>
<P>
 In Big West Conference softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific 4-4, Cal State Fullerton 2-2 -- Beth Corriea hit a grand slam in the 
fifth inning of the second game to help host Pacific (20-16, 7-5) complete the 
sweep. Corriea also had a hit and two RBIs in the first game. 
</P>
<P>
 Melissa Hadfield had a two hits, including a triple, and scored a run in the 
second game. Hadfield also had a triple in the first game. 
</P>
