<HEADLINE>
<P>
CULTURE WATCH; A VIDEO TRILOGY FOR LIFE WITH HIV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHARI ROAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The first of a planned trilogy of instructional videos for people with HIV is 
out from Lifeforce, a local nonprofit organization founded to help people with 
the disease. 
</P>
<P>
 The first tape, available for $39.95, focuses on diet and nutrition, said 
Lifeforce Director Steve Frankel. 
</P>
<P>
 A second video will explore holistic therapies and a third will look at 
various stress reduction techniques. 
</P>
<P>
 The diet video, titled "The HIV+ Survival Guide: Diet for Living in the Age of 
AIDS," does not endorse a particular protocol but deals with specific concerns 
of HIV-infected individuals, such as chronic fatigue, yeast infection and 
malnutrition. 
</P>
<P>
 Frankel said proceeds from the video sales will fund a free nutritional 
lecture series produced by Lifeforce. 
</P>
<P>
 The video can be purchased by calling (800) 788-8823. SHARI ROAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
