<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA HILLS; SCHOOL SAFETY TOPIC OF 1ST TOWN MEETING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A new community group will host a town meeting Thursday at Laguna Hills High 
School to discuss youth violence and school safety. 
</P>
<P>
 Community Action for Public Schools, a political action committee founded in 
December, has invited six panelists to the 7:30 p.m. meeting in the school's 
Little Theatre. 
</P>
<P>
 The panelists represent South County public schools, churches, law enforcement 
and county agencies. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will be moderated by the League of Women Voters and is the first 
in a series of town meetings the group will sponsor. 
</P>
<P>
 Suzie Swartz, the group's co-chairwoman, said the goal of the meeting is to 
ensure that the public schools remain a meeting ground and to inform the public 
on issues and people affecting public education. 
</P>
<P>
 "This town meeting is a call to all those who will work hand-in-hand to 
strengthen and improve our public schools," she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
