HALF-NAKED ESCAPEE IS LATER CAUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An inmate who escaped from the Peter J. Pitchess Honor Rancho and then -- clad 
only in his underwear -- allegedly robbed a woman of her car and jewelry was 
captured Sunday at a Palmdale motel, Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Timothy Ferhenback, 29, who was awaiting trial on a robbery charge, was 
reported missing late Saturday night, authorities said.A woman who lives near 
the jail reported that a man wearing only his undershorts and carrying a club 
broke into her house Saturday night and stole her jewelry and the keys to her 
car, sheriff's Deputy Benita Hinojos said. 
</P>
<P>
 Acting on a tip, sheriff's deputies scoured local hotels and motels and found 
Ferhenback with his girlfriend and her two children, said sheriff's deputy 
Angie McLaughlin. 
</P>
<P>
 The girlfriend, Kristie Hagen , 26, was booked on suspicion of harboring a 
fugitive, McLaughlin said. 
