<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BUENA PARK; SUPERVISORS TO SELECT NEW LIBRARY TRUSTEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Because the Buena Park Library District board could not decide last week who 
to select to fill a vacancy on its panel, the Board of Supervisors will select 
a new trustee, library director Colleen McGregor said. 
</P>
<P>
 The trustees had narrowed its choice to Carol Macera and Lucinda (Cindy) 
Alibrandi, both Buena Park residents. 
</P>
<P>
 But the supervisors are under no obligation to select either of the two 
finalists. 
</P>
<P>
 McGregor said it is hoped that the supervisors will make a selection within 30 
days. 
</P>
<P>
 The term of the vacated position expires in November, when the selected 
candidate would have to run for election to the board. 
</P>
<P>
 Eight candidates applied for the position vacated by Bill Hardin, who resigned 
after 13 years on the board. 
</P>
<P>
 Macera, a telephone operator and law student, has worked on political 
campaigns and was appointed as a delegate to the Democratic Central Committee. 
</P>
<P>
 Alibrandi, who holds a doctorate degree in psychology, is a Cypress College 
professor and director of the college's Human Services Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Board President Patricia Ganer and Trustee Robert Niccum voted to select 
Alibrandi. 
</P>
<P>
 Trustees Helen Bohen and Edward Erdtsieck favored candidate Macera. 
</P>
</TEXT>
