<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN KILLED IN SANTA ANA; BOYFRIEND HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TAMMERLIN DRUMMOND, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 34-year-old mother was killed early Sunday in the bathroom of her home 
during an argument with her live-in boyfriend, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police identified the woman as Laverne Victoria Montano of the 300 block of 
East Pomona Street in Santa Ana.Her boyfriend, identified by police as 
31-year-old Daniel Lopez, turned himself in to authorities several hours after 
the 12:30 a.m. incident, said Sgt. Don Robertson. He is being held on suspicion 
of murder. 
</P>
<P>
 According to police, Montano and Lopez began arguing after midnight. Lopez 
allegedly followed Montano into the bathroom, where the verbal argument turned 
physical; Montano was killed during the ensuing struggle, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 After the incident, Lopez allegedly ran out the back door. Some of the 
couple's roommates found Montano's body on the bathroom floor and called 
police, Robertson said. Police declined to release a cause of death, pending an 
autopsy. 
</P>
<P>
 The people who lived in the house with Lopez and Montano refused to discuss 
the incident. Some of the couple's neighbors on the quiet residential street 
said they were awakened by the woman's screams. 
</P>
<P>
 One woman, who asked not to be identified, said Montano's young daughter was 
in the house when her mother was killed. After the incident, the woman said, 
the girl ran into the street calling for someone to help her mother. 
</P>
<P>
 According to neighbors, two families shared the small, one-story house: 
Lopez's pregnant sister, her husband and four children, and Montano, her young 
daughter and Lopez. 
</P>
</TEXT>
