<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; MAN ARRESTED IN RAPE OF TEEN-AGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A short-order cook from Thousand Oaks was arrested early Sunday on suspicion 
of raping a 17-year-old youth from Thousand Oaks, Ventura County sheriff's 
deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
 Joaquin Franco, 38, who apparently befriended the victim last summer, made 
unwanted sexual advances toward the boy at about 1:15 a.m. Sunday while they 
were at the Janss Mall on Moorpark Road, Sgt. Raymond Nagel said. 
</P>
<P>
 Nagel said Franco and the youth are unrelated. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim rejected Franco's sexual advances but was overcome by physical 
force and assaulted, Nagel said. He was treated at Ventura County Medical 
Center and released, Nagel said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police responding to a 911 emergency call from an unnamed source spotted a man 
matching the description of the rape suspect, then apprehended Franco without 
incident. 
</P>
<P>
 Franco is being held at Ventura County Jail in lieu of $5,000 bail. He is 
scheduled to be arraigned Tuesday in Ventura County Municipal Court. JEFF 
McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
