Metro; Part B; Page 2; Column 4 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
174 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; RECREATION CENTER NEARS COMPLETION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Moorpark city officials say they are just one month away from finishing a 
$1.7-million recreation center at Arroyo Vista Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The city plans to hold a grand opening ceremony in June for the new facility, 
said Christine Adams, director of community services. 
</P>
<P>
 The new recreation center has a gymnasium and two multipurpose rooms, Adams 
said. The city plans to keep the facility open 80 hours a week for everything 
from adult basketball leagues to summer day camp for preschool-age children.  
</P>
<P>
 "We're hoping that the center can be used as much as possible," Adams said. 
</P>
<P>
 The city has spent about $3 million so far to develop about half of the 
69-acre park. 
</P>
<P>
 Along with the new recreation center, the money has been used to grade and 
landscape the grounds and install parking lots, Public Works Director Ken 
Gilbert said. 
</P>
<P>
 The city would like to add more than $15 million in improvements, including a 
lake, tennis courts and baseball diamonds, according to Gilbert. 
</P>
<P>
 "We might do that if we can ever find the money," he said. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
