<TEXT>
<P>
 Pager-Answering Machine Unveiled: Two companies unveiled a new pager in Dallas 
that acts like a pocket telephone answering machine.Motorola Inc. and Paging 
Network Inc., the country's largest paging company, say they expect to begin 
marketing the device nationwide next year, charging about $20 a month. Here's 
how it works: The person sending the message dials a special phone number, then 
hears a recorded greeting from the recipient and leaves a verbal message. This 
is sent by phone to a paging terminal, then to a satellite, and finally to the 
recipient. The recipient will hear a tone or feel a vibration from the device. 
