<P>
PACIFIC WATCH: AUSTRALIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Unemployment Declines, Jobs Grow: Australia's jobless rate in March fell to a 
seasonally adjusted 10.3% from 10.5% in February, its lowest point since 
November, 1991.Employment grew slightly, but not as much as analysts had 
expected. The drop in the jobless rate, however, was better than experts had 
predicted. The number of people employed in March rose by 7,100; that 
represented a drop of 8,800 in full-time jobs and a rise of 15,900 in part-time 
jobs. 
