<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: NEW JERSEY FIRM TO ACQUIRE LAPAROMED IN STOCK SWAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Privately owned Laparomed Corp. said it has agreed to be acquired by Advanced 
Surgical Inc. of New Jersey in an all-stock deal that will give Laparomed 
shareholders a 26.5% stake in the combined companies. 
</P>
<P>
 Terms were not disclosed, but the deal appears to be worth $10 million to $11 
million based on Friday's $3.75 per share closing price for Advanced Surgical 
stock in the Nasdaq Small-Cap market. 
</P>
<P>
 Both companies make and market instruments for so-called less-invasive, or 
laparoscopic, surgery. 
</P>
<P>
 Laparomed, with 10 employees, will continue to operate in Irvine as a research 
and development division of Advanced Surgical. Paul Lubock, Laparomed's 
president, will become senior vice president of Advanced Surgical. 
</P>
<P>
 Laparomed's majority owners are a group of venture capital companies that 
include Medicus Venture Capital in Menlo Park, Calif., and Cross Point Venture 
Partners in Irvine. 
</P>
